-- Immobel says holding company Allfin takes 29.85 pct stake
-- 
-- Fri Sep 19, 2014 08:59AM EDT
-- None



BRUSSELS, Sept 19 (Reuters) - Belgian real estate company Immobel <IMMO.BR> said on Friday that holding company Allfin Group had bought a 29.85 percent stake in the company.

Allfin paid 44.70 euros per share for the stake, which it purchased from Cresida Investment, another investor in Immobel. Immobel has a portfolio of offices and housing developments in Belgium in Luxembourg and is expanding into Poland.